<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-275-162  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 275 162.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  March 13 1989 v3 n11 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pentagon answers GAO weapons testing report. (General AccountingOffice)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Reed, Fred.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Pentagon contends that the GAO report on military testing ofweapons, issued Jul 26, 1988, is factually incorrect and that theGAO does not understand weapons testing.andP;  The GAO reported thattesting of the Army Helicopter Improvement Program, the Aquilaremotely piloted vehicle, the Conventional Tomahawk Land AttackMissile, the Aegis system, the Imaging InfraRed Maverick missile,and the Low-Altitude Navigation and Targeting InfraRed for Night(LANTIRN) system was inadequate and poorly conceived, and implieddishonesty in the presentation of the results.andP;  In a rebuttal, thePentagon has cited several errors of fact in the GAO report, aswell as asserting that there was a misunderstanding of what someof the tests were designed to do.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseUnited States. General Accounting OfficeWeaponsTesting.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>